Jonathan Greenblatt has been selected as the next National Director of the Anti-Defamation League (ADL), succeeding Abe Foxman. President Obama congratulates Greenblatt and expresses gratitude for his service as Director of the Office of Social Innovation and Civic Participation at the White House. The ADL has been a prominent voice against anti-Semitism and hatred for over a century, and Obama believes that Greenblatt will continue to uphold its legacy in promoting justice, freedom, and equality both in the United States and worldwide.